The paper describes the implementation of machine learning methods such as gradient boosted trees and recursive neural networks for clause guidance in automated theorem provers. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques and computational logic, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and software engineering (cs.SE).
